feed.message: There’s nothing like catching up with my neighbors on the street — hearing what’s on their minds, what’s in their hearts. The best policy ideas don’t start in boardrooms — they start on the block. #WoodhavenQueens

It was a beautiful day at the annual Woodhaven Street Fair with #TeamJenifer! I had a blast greeting hundreds of my neighbors. It’s a staple event every single year, celebrating our community and small businesses. Congratulations to Woodhaven Business Improvement District on another successful festival!
All of Woodhaven is out at the Annual Woodhaven Street Fair! Thank you to my neighbor for her warm words about my work 👇

Last night, I was proud to headline an event to support the Democratic Party’s slate in North Hempstead and Nassau County. Every day, I am grateful to be born in the greatest country on earth. This is election is a fight for the heart and soul of America. Let’s organize and WIN.

Today by the Statue of Liberty, I joined @GovKathyHochul and my colleagues to demand an end to Donald Trump’s reckless government shutdown. It’s irresponsible, harmful to working families, and puts New Yorkers’ livelihoods at risk. We need a government that works for the people. 

A shutdown means:
❌ Federal workers furloughed or forced to work without pay
❌ Delays for small business loans & housing programs
❌ Families waiting for food assistance & vital services
This is not leadership.

New Yorkers deserve a government that works for them, not one held hostage by chaos. It’s time to put people over politics, end the shutdown, and get back to serving the American people. 🇺🇸

G’mar chatima tova to New York's Jewish community observing Yom Kippur beginning tonight. I wish everyone a meaningful, reflective, and easy fast. May this Day of Atonement be one marked by forgiveness, mending of bridges, and improvement in the year ahead. #YomKippur
